      <h3>Why a clamp lamp beats a traditional base lamp</h3>
      <p>Traditional lamps eat 6-8 inches of precious desk depth. A clamp lamp gives you the same light coverage while keeping the entire surface clear for keyboard, mouse, and coffee. The LED strip design also spreads light more evenly across the desk than a single bulb.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Anyone with a small desk, dual-monitor setup, or shared workspace. Students in dorms and remote workers in apartments benefit most. It is not a reading lamp for beds, but for computer work, the directional light reduces glare on screens.</p>

